revision.text:
{{Infobox terrorist attack |title=2007 Yemen tourist attack |image= Yemen-Marib.png |caption= |location=[[Mareb]], [[Yemen]] |target=spanish Tourists |date=July 2, 2007 |time-begin= |time-end= |timezone=UTC+3 |type=[[Suicide attack|Suicide]] [[car bomb]]ing |fatalities=10 |injuries=12 |susperps= |perps=[[Al-Qaeda]] }} {{Campaignbox Insurgencies in Yemen}} {{Campaignbox al-Qaeda insurgency in Yemen since 1992}} The '''2007 Yemen tourist attack''' was a suicide car bomb attack on [[Spain|Spanish]] tourists visiting the [[Queen of Sheba]] temple in [[Mareb]], [[Ma'rib Governorate]] on July 2, 2007.
==Details== A member of [[Al-Qaeda]] rammed an explosive-laden car into a tourist convoy killing 8 Spanish tourists, 2 Yemeni Drivers, and injuring 12.<ref name=BBC>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/low/middle_east/6936999.stm|title=Yemeni tourist bombers ‘killed’|publisher=News.bbc.co.uk|accessdate=15 October 2014}}</ref>
==Aftermath== On August 8, four [[Islamic militants|militants]] died in a Yemeni security forces raid near Mareb, one of them [[Kassem al-Raimi]], who was the top al-Qaeda operative who masterminded the attacks. Raimi was involved in other operations and was one of 13 convicted prisoners who escaped from a [[Sana'a|Sanaa]] prison in 2006.
==See also== *[[List of terrorist incidents, 2007]] *[[Killing of British tourists in Yemen]] *[[2008 attack on tourists in Yemen]]
