'''''Herr Pastor''''' is a stereotypical [[authoritarian]] [[pastor]] in an [[Ethnic German]] congregation. ''Herr Pastor'', literally "Mister Pastor" in German, was a title often used even in English-speaking congregations with [[Germany|German]] heritage, such as [[Lutheran]] or [[Evangelical and Reformed Church]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Pastoral Concerns|url=http://www.leaderu.com/ftissues/ft9711/opinion/nuechterlein.html|website=www.leaderu.com}}</ref>
The leadership style of the ''Herr Pastor'' was, to some degree, a [[benevolent dictatorship]] in the sense that the ''Herr Pastor'' held supreme decision-making authority. Depictions of the ''Herr Pastor'' often characterise him as humorless.
